      "text": "The [[tetralemma]] or catuṣkoṭi [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catu%E1%B9%A3ko%E1%B9%ADi wikipedia], German sometimes called \"Urteils-Vierkant\", originates from Indian logic. Here it was first used in jurisdiction. It addresses the question of what positions can be taken with respect to 2 opposing parties."
