      "text": "These are the 4 positions of the tetralemma, whose application was later extended to metaphysical contexts. Nagarjuna, the founder of Madhyamika Buddhism, has criticized that these four positions are not the only possible ways of looking at things, but that there is, in addition, a fifth way of looking at things, which, however, is not a point of view, but reflexively negates itself. "
